  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (fb1f0aa 2022-08-30T00:04:46.258526Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe verify flag seems to get ignored while using with script for some reason. It used to work previously. This is how I invoke the script:\r\n`bash -c 'source .env && forge script DeployGoerli --rpc-url $GOERLI --private-key $GOERLI_PK --verify --etherscan-api-key $ETHERSCAN'`\r\n\r\nWhich deploys the contract successfully, but just ignores the --verify flag.\r\n[CMD output](https://pastebin.com/YmcpwPpH)\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's how my script looks like\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.16;\r\n \r\nimport { Script } from \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\nimport { HFD } from \"src/HFD.sol\";\r\n \r\ncontract DeployGoerli is Script {\r\n    function run() external {\r\n        vm.startBroadcast();\r\n        new HFD(1e18);\r\n        vm.stopBroadcast();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
